This ties into being able to easily update, add, and remove tags to any language we create in the future, as well as allows for the easy manipulation of Element classes.

We need a compiled list of all of the tags, attributes, and the way you assign the types.
We could also do with a compiled list of CSS elements for cross-language compatibility for future implementations.

During the initial stages of the creation of the project (first 36 hours) @christophercolumbusdog came up with a Python script that generated the CSS Styles as well as the generate function for the styles. We want to come up with a more generalized version of that, in which we can adapt it to working with other languages based on a template scheme. Should probably be in another Project as it doesn't pertain directly to the code to be used by others.

We can use any formatting we want for this, JSON would work, or if we want to come up with our own.
I was thinking something along the lines of
```
a
    href js{op} (string)
    media js{oa} cs{os} [all, print, screen, speech] (selection)
img
    align js{op} cs{os} [top,bottom,middle,left,right] (selection)
    alt js{op} (string)
```
If we choose the above method, we need docs explaining how everything works and what everything means.

The corresponding JSON: 
```json
[{
    "tag": "a",
	"attributes": [{
		"name": "href",
		"lang": [{
			"type": "js",
			"optional": true,
			"property": true,
			"attribute": false
		}, {
			"type": "cs",
			"optional": true,
			"property": true,
			"attribute": false
		}],
		"type": "string",
		"values": []
	},
	{
		"name": "media",
		"lang": [{
			"type": "js",
			"optional": true,
			"property": true,
			"attribute": false
		}, {
			"type": "cs",
			"optional": true,
			"property": true,
			"attribute": false
		}],
		"type": "selection",
		"values": ["all", "print", "screen", "speech"]
	}]
},
{
	"tag": "img",
	"attributes": [{
		"name": "align",
		"lang": [{
			"type": "js",
			"optional": true,
			"property": true,
			"attribute": false
		}, {
			"type": "cs",
			"optional": true,
			"property": true,
			"attribute": false
		}],
		"type": "selection",
		"values": ["top", "bottom", "middle", "left", "right"]
	},
	{
		"name": "alt",
		"lang": [{
			"type": "js",
			"optional": true,
			"property": true,
			"attribute": false
		}, {
			"type": "cs",
			"optional": true,
			"property": true,
			"attribute": false
		}],
		"type": "string",
		"values": []
	}]
}]
```

I personally am leading towards the custom one, a lot simpler to write, and its easily extendable.

We would also probably want a method of creating templates on how to build a class per language, that way as we need to, we can modify the template (maybe even a program to do this)

